<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 09 at 7:11PM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of west central
Scotland, southern Anson and south central Richmond Counties through
815 PM EDT...
At 711 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Wadesboro, moving southeast at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Wadesboro, Hamlet, Gibson, Lilesville, Morven, McFarlan and Diggs.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
